To get the action bar size in dp (density-independent pixels), you can modify the GET_ACTION_BAR_HEIGHT method in the following way:

1. Keep the current calculation to get the size in pixels.
2. Add a conversion from pixels to dp using the device's display metrics.

Here's the updated method:

```java
static void GET_ACTION_BAR_HEIGHT(Context context)
{
    TypedValue tv = new TypedValue();
    if (context.getTheme().resolveAttribute(android.R.attr.actionBarSize, tv, true))
    {
        int pixelSize = TypedValue.complexToDimensionPixelSize(tv.data, context.getResources().getDisplayMetrics());
        float density = context.getResources().getDisplayMetrics().density;
        int dpSize = (int) (pixelSize / density);

        ACTION_BAR_HEIGHT = dpSize;

        Log.d("ActionBarHeight", "Action bar height in dp: " + ACTION_BAR_HEIGHT);
    }
}
```

This modification will store the action bar height in dp in the ACTION_BAR_HEIGHT variable. The log statement will output the size in dp for verification.
